<statement>
<image width="33%" pi:generated="problems/images/2ae9979ee005023758e85360dbe4bfbf.png"/><p>
Suppose a = 7 and A = 25 degrees. Calculate:</p>
<p>
b = <fillin characters="20"/></p>
<p>
c = <fillin characters="20"/></p>
<p>
B = <fillin characters="20"/> degrees</p>
<p>
Round all answers to one decimal place.  Give angles in <em>degrees</em>
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>15.0</li><li>16.6</li><li>65.0</li></ul></p><p>First calculate the length of the other leg.</p>
<p>For the length of the other leg,</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\tan{{\left({25}\right)}}}=\frac{{7}}{{b}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{b}=\frac{{7}}{{\tan{{\left({25}\right)}}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{b}\approx{15.011548443567}\approx{15}</m>.</p>
<p>For the third side</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={7}^{{2}}+{15.011548443567}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={49}+{225.34658667356}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={274.34658667356}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}=\sqrt{{{274.34658667356}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}\approx{16.563411082067}\approx{16.6}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle B</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{B}={180}^{\circ}-{90}^{\circ}-{25}^{\circ}\approx{65}^{\circ}</m></p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>